SUMMARY:National BBCB Summit
LOCATION:333 South Franklin St Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:For event details: Home - 19th Annual National BBCB Summit (ht
 tps:nam04.safelinks.protection.outlook.com?urlhttps3A2F2Fweb.cvent.com2Fev
 ent2F11f056fc-3581-400e-853a-34859691a6a02Fsummary data057C027Cahouston144
 0hccfl.edu7C834a461f49d84e35d66308de3e52a36c7C6c031f94c402433a92d22d3ce851
 6da37C07C07C6390167218243912787CUnknown7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRyd
 WUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ3D3D7C07C
 7C7C sdatacsC2FdxbTrc2BsUAIQu4v0l6tpNjFCAtI0AQwtMk8TCXM3D reserved0) The 1
 9th Annual National BBCB Summit will take place March 4-7\, 2026. Staying 
 true to our mission\, BBCB  now known as: Believe. Build. Complete. Become
 .  remains deeply committed to advancing college completion and paving a s
 moother path to student success and has grown into a leading national even
 t that is open to all students of any background. After 19 years\, the Sum
 mit has been successful in attracting some of the most influential speaker
 s and scholars to address barrier that affect persistence and completion a
 mong college students. A series of theme-based workshops on contemporary p
 rovide an important focus to the Summit\, bringing together college studen
 ts and practitioners to engage in dialogue about critical issues\, sharing
  successful strategies and best practices. The 2026 Summit promises to be 
 another exciting event featuring Blair Underwood at the Dr. Sylvia Marion 
 Carley luncheon\, with an additional eight nationally acclaimed speakers i
 ncluding Damola Adamolekun \, Nigerian business executive and current chie
 f executive officer of Red Lobster Investor Holdings as well as Mark Dean 
 \, former IBM computer engineer whose most notable accomplishments include
  co-creating the IBM personal computer released in 1981. Most importantly\
 , BBCB creates unique opportunities and special student sessions for over 
 400 participants for over 150 educational institutions\, and 800 community
  members attend. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/178141
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/178141
END:VEVENT
